BIB                 10         28
TITLE      Activation measurement of the 3He(4He,gamma)7Be
           reaction
AUTHOR     (H.Volk,H.Kravinkel,R.Santo,L.Wallek)
REFERENCE  (J,ZP/A,310,91,1983)
INSTITUTE  (2GERMST)
FACILITY   (DYNAM,2GERMST) Dynamitron-Tandem-Accelerator
SAMPLE     A gas target of 4He
METHOD     (ACTIV) Three different activation measurements were
           made.
DETECTOR   (GELI,GE-IN) Two detectors were used: one Ge(Li),
           80 ccm, and one intrinsic Ge, 80 ccm, both with a
           resolution of 1.7 keV at Eg=1.3 MeV. For determining
           the detector efficiencies the available calibrated
           sources (152Eu, 22Na, 54Mn, 60Co, 133Ba) turned out
           to be too intense for the small distances between
           source and detector (25-30 mm).
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1,,1.) Uncertainty in total number of incident
           4He particles
           (ERR-2,4.5,8.3) Uncertainty in the cross section
           including errors in B(E) and the determination of E
           (ERR-3,3.7,4.3) Uncertainty in the number of produced
           7Be atoms including statistical errors, uncertainties
           in the efficiency of gamma-detectors and error of the
           branching ratio (see ANALYSIS).
           (ERR-T) Total error
HISTORY    (19871215C) Compilation produced by Arzamas RFNC-VNIIEF
           (19990315U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20250904A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
